  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, the monsoon season makes me sleepy too, I often crave a warm cup of tea to stay awake. How are you feeling today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Today I feel hopeful, because I revised 30 important topics for my NEET exam. But still lots to study, so a bit anxious. Chai is my best friend during study time. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Good to hear you're revising, that’s progress!\" \"Chai is a great study companion. What’s your go to recipe for study sessions?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually make ginger tea with a bit of turmeric and honey. It helps me stay awake and feel calm. Sometimes I add a biscuit—namkeen, actually. You? What do you drink when you study?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, ginger tea is a great pick, very grounding.\" \"Turmeric and honey are perfect for focus. What kind of namkeen do you prefer?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like bhujia or sev with tea. The crunch helps me stay alert! But I don’t eat too much—exam prep is serious! 😅 What about you, Maya? Do you snack while working?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Same here, a little crunch keeps things light. What’s your study music?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I listen to classical music mostly, like Hindustani ragas. It calms my mind. Sometimes I can’t focus without it. But it’s tough to study when I’m too distracted! 😅 I should go now—need to revise more. Thanks for chatting!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it, ragas help me too, they’re like a quiet focus helper. Did you try the biryani recipe I shared?\""
    }
  ],
